<item>
            <title>[QPID-1053] QpidTestCase should use something smarter than Thread.sleep(1000) to ensure that an external broker is listening on the port</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-1053</link>
                <project id="12310520" key="QPID">Qpid</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently QpidTestCase does a Thread.sleep(1000) to give the externally launched broker time to bind to the port. On slower systems, or when the broker has to go through recovery, this may not be long enough. This should be replaced with a check against the broker output to guarantee that the broker is ready.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
